# Focus Mode C(AF-C)

5

| Option | Description | Sample image |
| --- | --- | --- |
| SINGLE POINT | Focus tracks subject at selected fo- cus point. Use for subjects moving toward or away from camera. |  |
| [] ZONE | Camera tracks focus in selected fo- cus zone. Use for subjects that are moving fairly predictably. | ■ FIN |
| TRACKING | Focus tracks subjects moving through wide area of frame. |  |
| ALL ALL | Rotate the rear command dial in the focus-point selection dis- play ( 目 97, 99) to cycle through the AF modes selected for AF AF/MF SETTING > AF MODE ALL SETTING. MF | Rotate the rear command dial in the focus-point selection dis- play ( 目 97, 99) to cycle through the AF modes selected for AF AF/MF SETTING > AF MODE ALL SETTING. MF |
